==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Triangulate
<hw>Tri*an"gu*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Triangulated</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Triangulating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To divide into
triangles; specifically, to survey by means of a series of triangles
properly laid down and measured.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make triangular, or three-cornered.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Triangulation</ent>⟦br⟧
